Bio Prince Gundakar of Liechtenstein

Prince Gundakar of Liechtenstein is a member of the royal family of the tiny European principality of Liechtenstein. Born on April 1, 1949, he is the second son of Prince Franz Joseph II and Princess Gina of Liechtenstein. As a member of the sovereign family, Prince Gundakar holds the title of Prince of Liechtenstein and is a prominent figure in the country's royal household. Prince Gundakar of Liechtenstein is known for his involvement in various charitable and cultural organizations in Liechtenstein. He has supported numerous initiatives aimed at preserving the cultural heritage of the principality and promoting the arts. As a member of the royal family, he has been involved in various state functions and ceremonies, representing Liechtenstein both domestically and internationally. Overall, Prince Gundakar of Liechtenstein is a highly respected member of the royal family and a significant figure in the political and cultural life of Liechtenstein. Through his philanthropic activities, cultural initiatives, and political engagements, he has made a lasting impact on the principality and has helped to shape its identity as a unique and vibrant European nation.
